'''Energetic materials''' are a class of material with high amount of stored [[chemical energy]] that can be released.<ref>https://web.archive.org/web/20110720000157/http://undergradresearch.missouri.edu/forums-conferences/abstracts/abstract-detail.php?abstractid=843</ref>

Typical classes of energetic materials are e.g. [[explosive]]s, [[pyrotechnic composition]]s, [[propellant]]s (e.g. [[smokeless gunpowder]]s and [[rocket fuel]]s), and [[fuel]]s (e.g. [[diesel fuel]] and [[gasoline]]).

